Práctica 2¶

  • Mitchell Mirano Caro

Vamos a resolver la siguiente EDP de manera discreta $$u_{tt}(x,t) = u_{xx}(x,t) + e^{-t}, x \in [0,\pi] 1$$

$$u(0,t) = e^{-t}$$$$u(x,0) = 3\sin(x) +1 = f(x) $$$$ u_t(x,0) = -1 = g(x) $$$$u_x(\pi,t) = -3\cos(t) $$

Siguiendo el método implicito

con la forma:

$$Au^{j+1} = Bu^{j-1} + 2u^{j} + C$$
In [ ]:
using Printf, LinearAlgebra, Plots

Programando el Método de Crou para resolver un sistema tridiagonal

In [ ]:
function lu_descomposition(A::Tridiagonal{Float64, Vector{Float64}})
    
    n = length(A[1,:])
    L = zeros(n,n)
    U = zeros(n,n)

    
    L[1,1] = A[1,1]
    U[1,1] = 1
    U[1,2] = A[1,2]/L[1,1]

    for i in 2:n

        if i < n
            U[i,i] = 1
            L[i,i-1] = A[i-1,i]
            L[i,i] = A[i,i] - L[i,i-1]*U[i-1,i]
            U[i,i+1] =A[i,i+1]/L[i,i]
        end

        if i == n
            U[i,i] = 1
            L[i,i-1] = A[i-1,i]
            L[i,i] = A[i,i] - L[i,i-1]*U[i-1,i]
        end

    end
    
    return L, U
end

function crou_method(A::Tridiagonal{Float64, Vector{Float64}},b::Vector{Float64})
    
    n = length(b)
    L,U = lu_descomposition(A)
    
    z = zeros(n)
    z[1] = b[1]/L[1,1]

    for i in 2:n
        z[i] = b[i]/L[i,i] - L[i,i-1]*z[i-1]/L[i,i]
    end

    x = zeros(n)
    x[n] = z[n]

    for i in n:-1:2
        x[i-1] = z[i-1] - U[i-1,i]*x[i]
    end

    return x

end

a,b = 0,π
t_min, t_max = 0,1.5

α = 1
xn = 10
tn  = 100

h = (b-a)/xn
k = (t_max-t_min)/tn 
λ = k*α/h

cc_x0(t) = exp.(-t)
ci_f(x) = 3*sin.(π*x) .+ 1 
ci_g(x) = .-1
